<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 3:14PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...Lowering Visibilities Expected Tonight as Fog Re-Develops...
As of 300 PM Tuesday...areas of locally dense fog were confined to
the Connecticut River Valley and the southern and eastern
coastlines. However fog is expected to re-develop again as soon as
sundown and continue into the overnight hours across a large
portion of Southern New England. Visibilities are expected to drop
into the one-half to 2 mile range in many locations, although
some areas may experience visibilities of one-quarter mile or
less. A Dense Fog Advisory may be issued if visibilities drop to
one-quarter mile or less across a large portion of the area.
Be prepared for sudden changes in visibility in foggy areas. Use
low beam headlights and keep a safe distance between you and the
vehicle ahead of you.</description>
